Name.subject: Bunche, Ralph J. (Ralph Johnson), $d 1904-1971|~|United Nations--Cyprus|~|Makarios, III, Archbishop of Cyprus, 1913-1977
Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. Library. Department of Special Collections
Description.note: Digitization took place as part of the California Cultures Project.|~|On verso of photograph: UN 84460, Nicosia, Cyprus, 8 April 1964. Ralph J. Bunche, Under-Secretary for Special Political Affairs, met with President Makarios on 8 April 1964, during his visit to Cyprus. Mr. Bunche visited Cyprus in the course of a routine visit to study the problems and needs of the United Nations truce supervision and peace force operations in Gaza, Cyprus and Kashmir on instructions from the Secretary-General. The missions include the United Nations Emergency Force (UNEF), the United Nations Force in Cyprus (UNFICYP) and the United Nations Military Observer Group in India and Pakistan (UNMOGIP). Includes the following description of photograph: Dr. Ralph J. Bunche (left) Under-Secretary for Special Political Affairs, conferring with Archbishop Makarios, President of the Republic of Cyprus, in the Presidential Palace in Nicosia.
Title: Ralph J. Bunche confers with President Makarios

Name.subject: Bunche, Ralph J. (Ralph Johnson), $d 1904-1971|~|Vigier, Henri
Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. Library. Department of Special Collections
Name.photographer: United Nations. Dept. of Public Information
Description.note: Digitization took place as part of the California Cultures Project.|~|On verso of photograph: UN.20836.--The United Nations Acting Mediator, Dr. Ralph J. Bunche, signs the General Armistice Agreement between the Egyptian and Israeli Governments. At right is his political advisor, Henri Vigier. The agreement was concluded after several weeks of negotiations under the chairmanship of the UN Acting Mediator. Hotel de Roses, the Island of Rhodes. 24 February 1949.
Title: Egyptian-Israeli Armistice Agreement signed
